comment:
This is definitely a biased opinion because like everyone else, I do have my own preferences. So, I would say that if Mr. Beast and Pewdiepie uploaded today, I would watch Pewdiepie no question. In fact, I would watch JJ instead of Mr. Beast any day also.

 Chill, down to earth videos where there is a person sitting in front of their camera, in their room, and making entertainment is what personifies and manifests the spirit of a ‚Äúyoutuber‚Äù for me. 

Youtube has obviously evolved, with Mr. Beast revolutionising what it means to be a youtuber, he has taken it to new heights and nobody can take that away from him. But, Mr Beast to me, is not a ‚Äúyoutuber‚Äù in the classical sense, or at least he does not personify everything I loved and still love about youtube. 

If we could divide youtube into eras, Pewdiepie is the king of the era of youtubers who made entertainment with just the use of their camera, content and personality. On the other hand, Mr. Beast is the king of the era of youtube where entertainment is made through the use of great resources, lots of money, people, editors, and having a keen eye for what the audience feeds on. 

Pewdiepie‚Äôs era is characterised by people who did what they loved from the comfort of their room, Mr. Beast‚Äôs era is characterised by people who made youtube into an entertainment business.
